SIMPLE: ilang-ilang
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ilang-ilang
<hw>ilang-ilang</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An oil distilled
from flowers of the ilang-ilang tree, used in perfumery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An evergreen Asian tree (<spn>Cananga odorata</spn>)
with aromatic greenish-yellow flowers yielding a volatile oil; widely
grown in the tropics as an ornamental.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ylang-ylang, <spn>Cananga odorata</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ile</ent>⟦br⟧
